related failures that never surfaced locally\nbecause H2 (used by the unit tests) doesn't enforce either restriction\nthat Postgres does:\n\n- GET /api/metadata (export, @Transactional(readOnly = true)) got a\n  409: \"cannot execute UPDATE in a read-only transaction\" -- Postgres\n  actually puts the connection in a read-only transaction and rejects\n  any DML flush() might emit, even with nothing of ours to write.\n- GET /api/userRoles/{id}?fields=users[*] got a 409: \"No EntityManager\n  with actual transaction available for current thread\" -- by the time\n  applyUserSummaries runs during the deferred streaming JSON write,\n  there's no active transaction bound to the thread at all.\n\nBoth call sites only need the flush for read-your-own-writes\nconsistency after our own membership writes, which never happen from\na read-only or transaction-less context in the first place. Guard the\nflush with TransactionSynchronizationManager (matching the existing\nidiom in HibernatePeriodStore) so it only runs when there's an active,\nwritable transaction to flush.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 5 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","author":{"name":"Jason Pickering","email":"jason@dhis2.org"},"id":"6dd8512c4569cd77ba6ceba567c4eb62485a3dbb","tree_id":"1b4f5e1f4c80e6b6eaaf41f1a4b8d6acd1949407","timestamp":"2026-07-20T18:23:56Z","committer":{"name":"Jason Pickering","email":"jason@dhis2.org"}},"workflow_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/workflows/10954","repository":{"id":66940520,"node_id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnk2Njk0MDUyMA==","owner":{"login":"dhis2","id":1089987,"node_id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjEwODk5ODc=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1089987?v=4","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2","gravatar_id":"","type":"Organization","site_admin":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/events{/privacy}","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/following{/other_user}",